By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  Nigeria on Wednesday recorded 543 new cases of COVID-19, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. This is coming as the health agency said that a total of 813 lives have been lost to the novel virus since the index case in February with 15,815 patients treated and discharged. The NCDC’s report released via its twitter handle further revealed that a total of 38, 344  cases have been confirmed and are receiving treatments in different isolations across the federation. Below is the details of the report as released by the NCDC: Lagos-180 FCT-86 Kaduna-56 Edo-47 Ondo-37 Kwara-35 Ogun-19 Rivers-19 Kano-17 Ebonyi-16 Enugu-16 Delta-7 Bayelsa-4 Bauchi-3 Abia-1 38,344 confirmed 15,815 discharged 813 deaths. The breakdown of cases by state can be found Below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Lagos state, Kwara and Federal Capital Territory top the list of COVID-19 infections on Tuesday as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control confirmed 576 new cases of the dreaded virus in Nigeria. The health agency in its report released via its twitter handle… July 22, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Abujah Racheal ABUJA - The number of COVID-19 cases in Nigeria has reached 37, 225, the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports. According to the latest data released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, (NCDC) on its official twitter handle on Monday, 562 new cases were reported. The… July 21, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -Lagos state on Monday recorded the highest number of infections with 156 cases as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control confirmed that 595 new persons tested positive. According to the released report, the total confirmed cases in the country is now 33,153 while total… July 14, 2020 In "News"